With this in mind, I will interpret the Code to the effect that the subsequent spelling (
jejuna
) and the attribution (to Fabricius’s 1787 work) are to be preserved, and that this subsequent spelling is deemed to be the correct original spelling. This is also the spelling used by Fabricius in his own handwriting on the only preserved label ( Fig. 126 ) on any of the three syntypes in NHMD .

Thompson & Pont (1994: 84, under
ieiuna
) accepted Townsend’s (1931b) opinions and stated that a “HT ♀ ” is in “ UZMC ” (= NHMD ). I do not accept this claim. There is no holotype in NHMD or elsewhere, only syntypes .
